		<div class="courseListDescription">This workshop course, especially designed for students studying public health, occupational health, and social work, stresses effective communication in professionally relevant forms and contexts. The course explores the complex relationships between communicators, audiences, and varying discursive practices. Students will be introduced to fundamental concepts of rhetoric, document design, professional writing, research, and analysis and use them to persuasively communicate discipline-specific information and goals to diverse audiences.</div>
	
	
