    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/communication/CMN/210.html" title="CMN 210 - Text, Image and Sound" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">CMN 210</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Text, Image and Sound</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">In contemporary culture, we are surrounded by media and artifacts that attempt to persuade us to buy, believe or behave in certain ways. This course provides students with the analytical tools to understand the ways that text, image and sound work together to create persuasive objects. Using concepts from a wide range of theoretical frameworks related to communication, this course focuses on the design and use of media and messages in contemporary culture and the ways that text, image, and sound interact to create meaningful experiences.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
