    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/communication/CMN/213.html" title="CMN 213 - Texts in Social Contexts" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">CMN 213</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Texts in Social Contexts</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription"><p>All texts occur in social contexts. They emerge from and affect their communities of practice. This course provides students with the conceptual tools needed to investigate both the textual (written, oral, visual) and social practices associated with professional communication. Using concepts from genre theory, rhetoric, linguistics and semiotics together with concepts from social theories such as activity system theory and actor-network theory, students will explore issues related to power, agency and ethics in professional communication.</p>
</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
