    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/communication/CMN/215.html" title="CMN 215 - Messages, Modalities and Media" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">CMN 215</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Messages, Modalities and Media</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">The ability to interpret messages across modalities and media critically is fundamental to the transformation of information into meaningful knowledge. Using principles of discourse analysis and incorporating a range of examples and exercises, students will learn to identify, select, evaluate, and synthesize written and oral messages in ways that recognize the embeddedness of the interpretive process within its larger ethical, social, political and technological dimensions.</div>
	
	
