    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/communication/CMN/216.html" title="CMN 216 - Communication Revolutions" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">CMN 216</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Communication Revolutions</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">Both old and new communication technologies, through "revolutions" or epochs of advancement, have transformed modern culture. From the origins of language to the invention of communication technologies, such as writing, the printing press and the Internet, this course explores the origins, reception and uses of new forms of communication in their historical contexts with attention to their social, political, cognitive and technological impacts.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
