    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/communication/CMN/269.html" title="CMN 269 - Countercultural Communication" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">CMN 269</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Countercultural Communication</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">This course examines the complex relationships between conventional and countercultural communication practices. Investigating countercultural forms, spaces, and acts such as graffiti, comix, memes, zines, culture jamming, body modification, viral videos, and others, the course considers how novel and often subversive communication practices influence and alter conventional forms. Countercultural communication can drive innovation; its original voices, forms, practices and idioms can be adapted and applied to bring new life and power to conventional contexts and forms.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListWeight"><span class="courseInfoLabels">GPA weight: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">1.00</span></div>
	
	
