    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/communication/CMN/315.html" title="CMN 315 - Issues in Organizational Communication" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">CMN 315</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Issues in Organizational Communication</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">Effective communication has always been an essential component of business. It is particularly important today, when business people communicate in increasingly complex and diverse workplaces. They must deal with ethical dilemmas, intensifying organizational change, global and multicultural partners, increased specialization, and constant technological developments. Using practical examples and case studies, this course both explores communication challenges that business professionals face today and helps them develop strategies and practices designed for the contemporary workplace.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 2 hrs. Lab: 1 hr. </span></div>
	
	
