    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/communication/CMN/321.html" title="CMN 321 - Tech Comm as Knowledge Translation" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">CMN 321</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Tech Comm as Knowledge Translation</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription"><p>Technical communicators are often involved in the practice of knowledge translation. Working with other subject matter specialists technical communicators are charged with assisting in developing new knowledge (digital, medical, scientific etc.) but also with sharing that knowledge with other often non-technical audiences. Using rhetorical (text and image) and linguistic perspectives, this advanced course offers students the opportunity to investigate, practice and critique the genres and practices associated with technical communication.</p>
</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
