    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/communication/CMN/324.html" title="CMN 324 - Strategic Storytelling in Industry" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">CMN 324</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Strategic Storytelling in Industry</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">Stories are vibrant forms of expression that can engage others, promote values, encourage creativity, and inspire action. Students will learn the power and craft of storytelling as a professional communication strategy. Students will analyze basic concepts of narratology, examine case studies that illustrate a range of storytelling principles and practices, master a set of techniques for successful storytelling, and consider how new technologies suggest new ways of telling stories.</div>
	
	
