    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/communication/CMN/403.html" title="CMN 403 - Visual Semiotics" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">CMN 403</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Visual Semiotics</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">Every day, we are bombarded by an array of visual messages in the world around us.  We meet these images with an equally remarkable number of responses. This course focuses on this very phenomenon.  It addresses how images are meaningful, manipulative, and connected with the communicative discourses that govern them. It explores visual semiotics and discourse through the work of many writers including Charles Sanders Peirce, Roland Barthes and many contemporary writers.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 2 hrs. Lab: 1 hr. </span></div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListWeight"><span class="courseInfoLabels">GPA weight: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">1.00</span></div>
	
	
