    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/communication/CMN/447.html" title="CMN 447 - Communication and Law" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">CMN 447</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Communication and Law</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">Communication practitioners must understand how law matters in every day communication and be cognizant of the principles, institutions, and practices that regulate communication in a range of media and contexts. In this case and theory-based course, students explore the intersections of communication and law through the study of semiotics and legal discourse; the social and technological contexts of communication that provoke and challenge legal regulation; freedom of expression; and the legal frameworks for the protection of consumers, individual privacy, and intellectual property in the digital age.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lab: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListWeight"><span class="courseInfoLabels">GPA weight: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">1.00</span></div>
	
	
