    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/communication/CMN/448.html" title="CMN 448 - Introduction to Visual Communication" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">CMN 448</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Introduction to Visual Communication</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">This course introduces students to the study of visual communication. Students will examine the ways visual images persuade us to act, think, and feel, and will also learn vocabulary, concepts, and histories related to visual meaning-making. Students will focus on the ways images, seeing, and being seen influence the ways we experience the world within professional and social contexts and how visual images and image-making manipulate and become manipulated by a surrounding visual culture.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListWeight"><span class="courseInfoLabels">GPA weight: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">1.00</span></div>
	
	
