           <li class="courseListItem" style="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;padding:0 0 10px;list-style-image:none;list-style-type:none;">
           









  
    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/communication/CMN/450.html" title="CMN 450 - Participatory Media and Communication" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">CMN 450</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Participatory Media and Communication</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">Students will investigate theoretical and technological facets of participatory culture. Internet users have the ability to take part in digital conversations on topics ranging from entertainment to politics. Skills in the composition of text, image, and audio are developed through the production of digital media. These compositional and technical skills will develop strategies that move consumers of media to become media producers participating in digital dialogues. Students will also explore ethical aspects of participatory culture.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 2 hrs. Lab: 1 hr. </span></div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListWeight"><span class="courseInfoLabels">GPA weight: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">1.00</span></div>
	
	
